      "role": "user",
      "content": "there is no light. that's the thing. it's not like i'm just in a dark room waiting for the sun to come up. it's like the sun itself is gone. i look at the empty side of the bed and i just feel like a shell. like i'm just going through the motions of a life that doesn't even belong to me anymore. it feels so pointless to just keep dragging this weight around every single day.",
